adviseScripts.text: Since ancient times, cats have been a symbol of good luck for sailors.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I heard that having a feline companion on board can even ward off shipwrecks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: What do you think, should we get a cat for the Admire?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Will the cat be able to get along with Morgan?
Maybe we can ask Nero to help us out.
Oh shoot, I hadn't thought of that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Well, Morgan is pretty understanding, so I'm sure it'll work out somehow.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Hey, that's a great idea!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Ahaha! You're such a genius, Captain!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I'll go look for a cat tree to put on the ship!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: We look into the process of adopting a cat,
but the complicated procedures and expensive fees make it too difficult for us to follow through.
What's the deal with all this dust?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I keep sweeping and wiping, but it just keeps coming back.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: With that kind of resilience, it could probably beat a sea monster easily.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: You're pretty impressive for being able to handle it.
How about getting a robot vacuum?
Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: You're right. I do manage to get rid of it every time it pops up.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Maybe that means I'm at the top of the food chain!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: That's actually a great idea.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Although, I don't think the Admire is the right size for it...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Anyway, I'll bring it up to Helm.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: We discuss mindset management in cleaning.
Ahoy, Captain!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Have you ever heard of the drifting ghost ship?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I don't like horror stories.
Tell me about it.
Ha, I thought you were braver than that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: How about giving it a chance?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Trust me, it's not so scary once you hear the story.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Well, as you know, no survivors have been reported upon the surface.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But some resource miners went to the coast and told me something interesting.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Beyond the foggy area,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: there's a huge warship that keeps flashing its searchlight, blink, blink...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Sending out an unknown signal before vanishing like a ghost ship!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Do you know what the signal says?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: "Aliens have appeared. We advise all citizens to take shelter."
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: When was the last time someone mentioned Raptures aliens anyway?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: It's been ages!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: With the lights off in the Commander's Room, I listen to Mast's story of the ghost ship.
Oh gosh, I'm so scared right now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I can't help but wonder where is Morgan's limit.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: It's hard to gauge, you know?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Morgan and me, which one do you like?
Did Morgan learn new phrases?
Captain, seriously?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Are you really competing with a bird right now?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Haha, you bet!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: C'mon, Morgan. Time to show Captain what you've learned!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Hey, why aren't you showing off for everyone else?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I spend some time feeding and playing with Morgan.
Hey, Captain.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: When do you think rum tastes the absolute best?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: When I'm drinking it with Helm.
When I'm drinking it without Helm finding out.
Hmm, yeah.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But scheduling a drinking session with Helm isn't easy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: She's always busy saving the world!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But when you finally do get to drink with her, it's always worth the wait.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Hmm, I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Knocking back a few while on the job can be fun too, I guess.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But drinking with your fellow crewmates is always more memorable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: It's always a night of celebrating stories and reminiscing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Mast's tales about all the epic adventures of the Aegis Squad.
Captain!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Do you wanna be my crewmate?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I am the captain, so technically you should be my crewmate.
Aren't we already crewmates?
Hm, that does make sense.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But really, does it even matter who's who as long as we're all in it together?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: If the ship goes down, we're all going down with it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Ahaha, yeah!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I just wanted to try saying
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: the famous line from Straw Hat Voyage to you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: It feels pretty great to say out loud, doesn't it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Mast tells me a story about a young boy with a dream of becoming the Pirate Lord.
I'm running late for my counseling session with Mast.
As I approach the Commander's Room, I hear someone singing.
Yo-ho! Yo-ho! A pirate's life for Mast and Morgan♪
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: We'll enjoy the pirates' feast until Captain comes♪
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Hahaha! I'm here to take over your ship!
Hahaha! Let's set sail and go on an adventure!
Wait, what? Aren't we on the same side?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: That's right! Hand over everything nice and easy!
Uh, um, you wouldn't really betray me, would you, Captain?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: You must have been cursed by some ancient dark magic.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Don't worry, I'll find a way to break it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Sure thing!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Let me finish up this pirate feast real quick, then we can board the ship!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: The winds are just right, this voyage is going to be amazing!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I play a loud and fun pirate game with Mast.
Captain, Morgan's been surprisingly chatty lately...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: What do you think he wants?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Maybe you haven't been playing with him enough?
Maybe you stole his food?
I don't think that's how it works.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: He's too wise to be entertained by mere games.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: It's more like he's playing with me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Hey, come on, Captain.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I would never steal a bird's food, no matter how hungry I am!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But, I may have snuck a taste of his jello when I was drunk on rum...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Best snack with alcohol! Best snack with alcohol!
adviseScripts.speaker: Morgan

adviseScripts.text: How many times did you do that for him to learn that phrase?
I listen to Morgan chatter on for a while.
Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: This might be a tough question to answer, but...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Captain, do you think I can become a pirate?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Whether or not they can achieve it, a true pirate chases their dream, isn't it?
Well, first you should probably take off that navy uniform.
Thanks, Captain.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I was starting to lose faith, but you reminded me why I started down this path in the first place.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: If I take this off, I'll lose the only remaining ship I have.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Won't that make me stray farther from my dream?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Mast and I talk about her career development.
A voyage always starts with gathering your crew!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: So, if you were going to set sail,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: who would be the first person you'd look for?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I'd have to find a parrot to be my lucky charm.
I'd have to find someone to sail the ship for me.
What? But...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I thought I was the one taking care of Morgan.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: It turns out I'm the one who relies on him more!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Haha, you know what you're talking about!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: And don't you worry, I'll always be here sailing with the Admire.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: If you're looking for adventure, don't go to anyone else. Make sure you come find me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Mast and I team up to form the ultimate voyage dream team.
Why did you join the Admire?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Was it for the thrill of adventure, the money, or your crewmates?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I wanted to take back the surface we lost.
I wanted to see new places I've never seen before.
Ah, I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: That's just like you, Captain. As firm and resolute as a rock.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Yes, that's exactly why I love sailing too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: For those of us who were born and raised in the Ark,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: the view from the ship's deck is priceless.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Mast and I discuss the true meaning of sailing.
You know, since the olden days,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: the most famous pirates were always known by their nicknames, not their real names.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: So, what do you think mine would be?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: The Last Voyager.
The Mean Pirate Queen.
Hmm, that sounds a bit melancholic, but also kinda cool.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: It reflects reality, but if it were up to me,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I'd strive to make the "last" the "first".
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Seriously? That's the best you could come up with?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: How about...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: The Ocean's Barrel! The Ocean's Barrel!
adviseScripts.speaker: Morgan

adviseScripts.text: You two are playing a trick on me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Mast and I seek to find a memorable nickname that truly represents her identity.
Being a pirate
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: is all about having amazing adventures and experiencing things that are out of this world!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Are there any legends or mysterious phenomena that you've always wanted to experience first-hand?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I want to explore the Devil's Triangle.
I want to come across a cursed pirate ship.
... The Devil's Triangle?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Alva particles in there are so dense
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: that it blocks all communication.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: And there are crazy tornadoes that destroy ships left and right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Actually, I've looked into that place too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I heard that some people fled there during the first invasion.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I wonder if they're still alive and kicking... I'm itching to go on an adventure there again!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Oh, I see what you're going for.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: You're talking about the outlaws' pirate ship that drifts eternally
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: because they're cursed for being too greedy, right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But isn't that just a Pirates of the Caspian rip-off?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Come on, Captain, use your imagination.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Mast and I indulge in our imaginations with enthusiasm.
Hey, did you ever hear that in the pirate world,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: it's kind of a tradition to have an animal companion like Morgan?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Do you have any animals that you trust, Captain?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I think a parrot is best for a pirate.
I think a monkey would be nice.
Parrots are the ultimate pirate companion, no doubt about it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Ummm, I don't know about that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: The monkey would probably play tricks on me,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: like leaving banana peels in my path or something...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Nah, a monkey just isn't for me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Mast and I discuss the importance of animal companions.
Anchor is a great crewmate, but sometimes she leaves me scratching my head.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Like, when we were cleaning, out of nowhere, she just yells, "Starfish!" What's up with that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Don't try to understand girls going through puberty.
Maybe that's Anchor's special code system.
I know other girls her age
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: and they don't act like that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But they always storm out of the room and slam the door behind them, saying not to follow.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Might as well cloak her in mystery
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: since we can't decipher her anyway, huh?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: That's not a bad approach.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: We discuss the peculiar behaviors of Anchor that we've observed so far.
Sometimes I feel bad for the Admire.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: It was built to be a majestic warship,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: racing across the open ocean, slicing through the waves.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But it's stuck dry-docked most of the time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I'll make sure we get out to sea soon.
That's why we're always stoked when an opportunity comes around.
Thank you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I want to help make that happen, too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But sadly, I don't have many means to do so.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Yeah, that makes sense.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: In fact, I get so pumped that I can't even sleep when I think about the possibility of unexpected adventures.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I bet the Admire feels the same way.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: We send an email to Andersen, expressing our desire for more seafaring missions.
Usually, famous pirates have rivals who are every bit as notorious.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: So who do you want to compete with the most, Captain?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Helm's enemy, starfish.
The humans' enemy, Rapture Queen.
Even though Helm doesn't know, she'd be so grateful if she found out about this.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But you're already a captain! Shouldn't you be dreaming bigger?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: That's what I call a pirate with plenty of potential! You're one ambitious captain!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Count me in, I'll be following you all the way until we crush all our rivals!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: We analyze the rivalries depicted in famous pirate movies.
Mast seems to have a lot on her mind.
Wait patiently.
Did anything happen?
... Captain.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I think I need to go somewhere.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: May I leave first?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Go ahead.
Are you not gonna ask why?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: We're crewmates who trust each other. No words needed.
Thanks so much. Let's have rum together next time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Yeah, things like this happen all the time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: The higher-ups always rush Helm, which forces Helm to rush us.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But this time, things are pretty dicey.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: If it's possible, I don't want to let you see me like this.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: We end the session early due to Mast's personal reasons.
Anchor is just so intriguing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Did you know that she has a radar inside her own body?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But it malfunctions sometimes
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: and she just bumps her head against the cabin wall to fix it. It's like it gets magically repaired or something.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I thought radars were supposed to have precise components?
I guess that's really the way to fix everything in this world.
Exactly!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I don't know what'll happen if more problems arise in the future,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: especially if she keeps fixing it like that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: What...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Uh, anyway, she often spaces out and gets lost in her own thoughts.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I just feel so intrigued when I watch her do that though.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: I spend some time listening to Mast talk about everything Anchor's radar can do, all 99 of them.
Is Deputy Chief Andersen your immediate boss?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: What's he like anyway?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: He's definitely worthy of respect.
He gives me way too much work. Does he think I don't have anything else to do?
Yeah, I can see that too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: He seems calm and mature,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: and he's reliable too—never goes back on his word.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: But you know, my superior, Burningum, isn't so bad either in those aspects.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Let me just say, I feel you, Captain. It's crazy how all employees feel the same way.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: Like, we work under Burningum,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: but it's also our job to manage the Admire.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: And he always forgets that fact.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mast

adviseScripts.text: We have a secret discussion about our superiors.
